column4: hi, I am having a HUGE problem with this computer. When I try to do a fresh install with a jaunty live CD,  I cannot boot from cd, I also cannot run the .exe once gutsy starts up.
I tried package manager update, but it is way out of date
needs to be redone
nickster04: how do I get the comp to install jaunty then?
Did you verify the CD using the verification option on the boot menu?
no how does one do that?
Does the CD boot at all?
What do you mean?
I mean I have installed from live cds dozens of times, and each time on startup, it runs the disc...not the O
but in this case I can only access it after GNOME loads
access being, read the disk?
yeah
What do you see on the disk, out of curiosity?
Casper, dists, install, isolinux, pics, pool, preseed, ubuntu, autoruninf, md5sum, README, wub1.exe
Alright, that sounds normal.  But, if it doesn't boot, it must not be.  Which iso did you download?
Jaunty amd64 live cd
the desktop CD?
I think so
And this is a 64bit computer?
I was told it is by the person who owns the computer, I cannot get info from the comp about what sort of processor is in it. I looked at the motherboard, and it is intel
but yeah, I think it is 64
even if it was not, it would still load cd on boot. hould I try a 32 bit?
I'd download the 32bit one, just to try it.  All 64bit machines will work with the 32bit one, yeah. i386 disk
I already have it,  I will try again
